# 🔥 Nakama Backend — Zero-Defect Agent Protocol

You are working on the **IntelliVerseX Nakama game backend** (Nakama 3.35.0, CockroachDB v24.1, TypeScript/JavaScript Goja ES5 runtime).

---

## 🚦 MANDATORY SESSION START — Do These First

Before touching ANY file, silently read (in this order):

1. **[`.agents/SKILL_BOOK.md`](.agents/SKILL_BOOK.md)** — keyword router, picks the right skill
2. **[`.agents/skills/<matched>/SKILL.md`](.agents/skills/)** — load ONLY the 1-2 skills that match the task
3. **Never read all skills** — budget is 2 skills max per task

---

## ⚡ Non-Negotiable Hard Rules (Memorize These)

| # | Rule | Consequence of Breaking |
|---|------|------------------------|
| 1 | **NEVER hand-edit `data/modules/index.js`** | Next `npm run build` overwrites silently |
| 2 | **TypeScript `target` MUST stay `"es5"`** | Goja VM crashes at runtime with cryptic errors |
| 3 | **No global-scope state variables** | Goja VM pool isolates each call — state is lost |
| 4 | **No Node.js built-ins** (`require('fs')`, `require('http')`, etc.) | postbuild.js skips the file entirely — RPC silently missing |
| 5 | **All RPC functions must be declared in global scope** | Nakama AST walker won't detect them — RPC not registered |
| 6 | **Env vars for JS MUST be in `RUNTIME_ENV_KEYS`** in docker-compose entrypoint | `ctx.env['KEY']` returns `undefined` with no error |
| 7 | **Always rebuild + restart after code changes** | Goja loads modules at startup only — changes invisible |
| 8 | **NEVER commit `.env` or credentials** | Security breach |

---

## 🏗️ Mental Model — How Code Flows

```
You edit:   data/modules/src/**/*.ts
            ↓ npm run build (tsc → es5 → build/index.js)
            ↓ node postbuild.js  (merge all .js + generate RPC wrappers)
Lives at:   data/modules/index.js  ← NEVER touch this
            ↓ docker volume mount → /nakama/data/data/modules/
            ↓ docker compose restart nakama
            ↓ Goja VM loads index.js at startup
Tested at:  http://localhost:7351  (Nakama Console API Explorer)
```

---

## 🔁 Zero-Defect Workflow (Follow Every Time)

```
PLAN   → Read SKILL_BOOK, load matched skill(s), grep project for context
CODE   → Write only in data/modules/src/**/*.ts or matched JS module
BUILD  → cd data/modules && npm run build
VERIFY → grep new RPC/function in data/modules/index.js  ← confirm it's there
RELOAD → docker compose restart nakama
TEST   → docker compose logs -f nakama (watch for goja errors)
        → Test via http://localhost:7351 API Explorer
DONE   → Zero console errors = ship
```

**If any step fails, STOP and fix before continuing. Never skip VERIFY.**

